    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single gap (Test conditions, achieved level 1 vs. required level 2) is acknowledged; however, the ASTM F1717 protocol prescribes a single standardized condition, and multi-laboratory testing across N=11 specimens provides sufficient confidence that the FEA model reliably predicts compression-bending behavior within the stated COU. All three QoIs satisfy pre-specified acceptance bounds. The overall credibility evidence supports an Accepted decision for regulatory submission.",
